Innodis of Mauritius Climbs Most in More Than a Year

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-02-15T11:18:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/innodis-of-mauritius-climbs-most-in-14-months-on-profit-surge.html
  Innodis Ltd ., Mauritius’s largest
food company by market value, rose the most in more than a year
after it said second-quarter profit through December almost
doubled.  The stock climbed 1.1 rupees, or 3.6 percent, to 32.10
rupees, the highest level since Dec. 29, by the 1:30 p.m close
in the capital,  Port Louis . The increase was the most since
January last year and follows a 1.3 percent rise yesterday.  The group’s profit increased to 70.4 million rupees ($2.4
million) compared with 36.1 million rupees a year earlier, the
Port-Louis based company said on Feb. 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
